have been validated experimentally at n-TOF (NIM/A,521)
*By authors*.The main improvement with respect to
previous measurements is because of an optimized
detection setup, by which the crucial neutron
Gamma-ray absorption effects inside the sample have
been corrected by employing a nonpolynomial weighting
function. The neutron sensitivity correction has to be
considered separately because it has been applied only
to one of the measured resonances. Although the
uncertainty of the correction was 20%, the
contribution to the systematic uncertainty of the
capture kernel was only 0.7% in this case.
